cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning approach that incorporates object-based priors and probabilistic modeling of environments, which are core topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of object features and object-contact priors also suggests a connection to computer vision and robotics. Finally, the focus on sample efficiency and rapid experimentation aligns with the goals of neural and evolutionary computing.
